[6] Australia (Sydney, Uluru): alert
Date: Mon 3 Feb 2020
Source: Daily Telegraph [abridged, edited]
https://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/newslocal/wentworth-courier/measles-warning-woman-visited-sydney-uluru-while-infectious/news-story/cef8fba2b0654c210d21fc62a241ee9a

A woman visited Uluru and multiple locations in Sydney while infectious with measles, leading to health authorities issuing a warning to the public.

It is the 10th case diagnosed in NSW since Christmas.

The woman spent time in Bondi Junction, Rose Bay and Double Bay while infectious between Sun 26 Jan and Fri 31 Jan 2020. She also travelled to Uluru for a day trip on Mon 27 Jan 2020.

[See URL above for a full list of places she visited while infectious. - Mod.LK]

Health authorities have issued a measles warning.

